|{{dts|format=dmy|2000|Jul|8}}
|{{failure}}
|This was the second end-to-end system test. The test was designed to target a mock warhead, transmitting its location by [[C band (IEEE)|C-band]], and ignore a single large decoy balloon. The failure to intercept occurred because the EKV did not separate from the boost vehicle due to an apparent failure of the [[MIL-STD-1553|1553 data bus]] in the booster.
